inn1.comm: good length delivery angled across, Richards lets it go through to Rahim behind the wicket.
pushed to the off side off the back foot.
angled across, bit wide outside the off stump, left alone once again.
on a good length and swinging in and Richards pushes it down the track.
too wide outside the off stump and signalled by the umpire Doctrove.
pushes forward of point off the back foot.
swinging in and turned away to short midwicket.
fuller on the pads and turned away to the onside to square leg for a single.
short outside the off stump, cut away down to third man for a single, width offered.
defended off the back foot to the off side.
forces off the back foot to the off side.
moves across to the off side and turns it off his wrists to the right of mid-on for a single.
pushes with a straight bat back to the bowler.
moves forward to a good length delivery and defends with an angled bat behind point.
moves into line and defends to short cover.
good length delivery defended to mid-off, a slower delivery.
good shot this time by Fletcher, picks up the length and cuts forward of point to the deep.
short ball pulled well forward of square leg for the first boundary of the innings.
slower delivery, good change of pace from Rasel, defended watchfully behind point.
just over the fielder at mid-on, a full delivery driven in the air over Ashraful and to the fence.
lovely delivery at the block-hole, just squeezes it out to third man, almost goes to the fence, good save by Rasel with his foot.
plays with an angled bat behind point to pick up a single.
plays to the right of mid-on to pick up another single.
chops it down to third man.
driven in the air and on the bounce to mid-off.
lofts it over the bowler for couple of runs.
turns it forward of square leg for a single.
slower delivery outside the off stump, plays and misses.
it is in the slot for Fletcher, who hits it high in the air down the ground and just bounces in front of the ropes for a boundary.
again in the slot for Fletcher, hits it well this time over mid-off, for another boundary.
played wide of midwicket for a single.
and he strikes first ball, tossed up and Fletcher looking for the big shot once, miscues it high in the air  and Naeem from cover turns and runs forward to take a good catch.
plays to the off side.
moves back and punches to cover.
a long hop this time from Shakib, Richards on the back foot picks it up and pulls well to midwicket fence.
turn and bounce for Shakib, beats the outside edge.
spins down leg, goes for the pull and misses it, takes it high on the pad.
moves back and plays it with an angled bat behind point for a single.
strikes high on the pad and pitched outside the leg stump, Rahim screams.
gets behind the delivery and defends to the off side.
too wide and lot of room for Richards, who cuts it in the gap behind point and the ball races away to the fence in quick time.
turned away forward of square leg to pick up a quick single as the fielder was pouncing on the ball.
a bad line this time from Rasel, on the legs and played fine past the short fine leg fielder and the ball rolls into the fence, was a poor effort from the fielder.
sweeps and misses, off the pad to the onside.
waits for the turn and plays to the onside.
driven back to the bowler to the left side of Shakib.
almost dragged it back to his stumps as the ball was too full for the drive.
defended watchfully this time to short cover.
comes forward and defends on the track.
looks to go forward but back and cuts hard to point but for no run.
driven to mid-off for a quick single, shy at the stumps and strikes it but the batsman is well in.
on the back foot and looking to work it to the onside, taken on the pad.
lovely delivery once again, spin and bounce, beats the outside edge as Richards looks to defend off the back foot.
played back down the track
looking to turn it to the onside, the spin beats the bat.
moves back and across and defends down the track.
drives off the front foot to mid-on, poor fielding by Mahmudullah, that single brings up the 50 for West Indies.
turned away to the onside.
once again played to the onside to the fielder at short midwicket.
turned away to the fielder at short fine leg.
strikes full on the legs down the leg side, loud appeal and turned down, was missing leg.
down the leg side, signalled a wide.
short ball pulled behind square leg to the deep, a mistimed shot, was actually looking to pull forward of square leg.

turned away to square leg and Richards takes off from the non-strikers end, a bad throw from the fielder, was too wide, Razzak fails to pick it up, the fielder backing up collects the ball and gets rid of the stumps at the bowlers end. A ridiculous run out.
defended to the off side.
turns it to short fine leg.
plays forward and with an angled bat plays to short third man.
lovely turn, spins away from the face of the bat to beat the outside edge.
plays forward and gets the edge to the onside.
hit in the air down the ground to long off.
moves forward and driven down the ground to long on for a single.
defended square of the wicket on the off side.
Another misunderstanding but the throw was bit slow as the ball was played to backward point and Shakib is absolutely furious.
turns it forward of square leg.
cut away hard to point.
turned away to deep square leg for a couple
on the leg stump, turns it to square leg for a single
fuller on the middle stump. Dowlin comes forward and defends
outside the leg stump. Dowlin defends it comfortably onto the pitch
outside off, looks to cut it away and is beaten
cut to deep point for a single
outside off. Pushes it to cover point off the back foot
on the leg stump, pushes it to midwicket
pulled to deep square leg for a single
turned away to deep backward square leg for a couple
left alone outside the off stump.
driven to mid-on for a single.
moves forward and works to midwicket.
spins down leg, plays it down to short fine, could not get it past the fielder.
spins in sharply and Smith looking for the cut is surprised by the turn.
swept down to fine leg for couple of runs.
defended to the off side.
worked away behind square leg to pick up a single.
moves back and plays to cover.
spins wide outside the off stump, cut hard but cannot get past the fielder at extra cover.
cuts and misses, a loud appeal from Rahim for a catch, turned down.
plays to the right of cover for a single.
down the leg side, off the pad to short fine leg.
moves back and turns it to square leg.
moves back and plays square of the wicket on the off side and looking for a single, sent back.
spins in and Dowlin plays to the onside.
again on the back foot, defended down the track.
comes forward and takes it on the pad as the ball spins in.
played to the left of the bowler to the onside.
waits on the back foot for the turn and works it behind square leg to pick up a single as Rahim goes after the ball.
short ball pulled around but no timing there as it was played to square leg.
this time he puts it away in style, he picks up the long hop and pulls well in the air to the square leg fence, got into a good position this time.
turns it behind square leg to pick up another single.
cuts straight to the fielder at point.
moves forward and drives down the ground to long on.
down the track and works it to mid-on for a single, Devon using his feet to the spinners, that is what we like to see.
a sharp single to short third man, the throw from Ashraful was bit high for Rahim.
plays with an angled bat to short third man for a single.
worked to forward of square leg.
spins down the leg side, was way down.
waits on the back foot and plays it down to long leg to pick up a single.
played to short fine leg but for no run.
quicker delivery played to short third man.
plays softly to the off side and looking for a single but Rahim quickly picks up the ball.
played to the off side to extra cover for a single.
moves back and plays to cover.
pushes it down the track and back to the bowler.
a leading edge high in the air and falls safely at long off, the fielder was bit deep.
cuts off the back foot to the sweeper in the deep on the off side..
played to the onside.
plays forward for the turn but the ball goes straight on, beats the bat.
turned to square leg for a single.
up on his toes and pushes to mid-off.
a sharp single to midwicket.
fires it in full and quickly, almost yorked himself as he looks to drive.
pulled away to deep midwicket.
off the pad to short fine leg.
comes forward and defends to the right of the bowler on the off side.
comes forward and plays with an angled bat to backward point.
played back down the track.
short ball pulled to deep midwicket.
too short once again, a long hop, pulled well over the midwicket fence for a maximum, the first six of the day, picked his spot nicely.
works it forward of square leg for a single, good running.
tossed up outside the off stump, driven down the ground to long on.
quicker delivery cut away to the sweeper in the deep on the off side, wonderful running, comes back for the second run.
looking for the pull and takes it high on the pad, loud appeal turned down.
turned away to the onside.
played behind point for a single.
worked to midwicket but straight to the fielder.
waits on the back foot and plays to backward point.
sweeps and misses the delivery down the leg side, wide signalled.
moves forward and drives past the fielder at short extra cover and to the deep to pick up couple of runs, that brings up the 100 for West Indies in the 24th over.
well played, short and wide, cut away behind point to the deep, Smith runs well and calls Dowlin for the third, putting pressure on the fielders.
plays and misses outside the off stump, a lazy shot that and playing away from his body.
full toss and a slower delivery, Smith misses the drive and through to Rahim.
opens the face off the bat and plays down to third man for a single.
short delivery on the legs, turned away to deep backward square leg for a single.
slower delivery, opens the face off the bat and plays to third man, another good piece of running as they put pressure on the fielder, gets back for the second run.
looking for the sweep and takes it on the body, an appeal from Shakib, which is turned down.
moves forward and pushes to the onside, a thickish edge.
cut behind point, it was the quicker delivery and too close for the cut shot.
moves forward and drives to extra cover.
moves forward and drives to the left of extra cover this time, good fielding there by Naeem.
once again played to extra cover.
short down the leg side, signalled a wide.
moves forward and drives down the ground to long off.
slower delivery and it was short, Dowlin fails to pick up the change of pace, just blocks it to the off side.
plays with an angled bat behind point and looking for the single, the fielder in quickly prevents the run.
slower delivery and it was full outside the off stump, moves across and and whacks it down the ground to long on.
short delivery pulled well forward of square leg to the deep for couple of runs.
another full delivery, driven down the ground to long off.
swept to short fine leg.
moves forward and drives past the midwicket fielder to the deep.
quicker delivery played to short third man.
moves forward and drives back to the bowler.
moves back and cuts along the ground to the sweeper cover for a single.
cuts hard along the ground to deep cover for a single.

low full toss turned forward of square leg outside the inner circle, Tamim running in from the deep does well to pick up the ball and score a direct hit to get rid of Devon Smith as he was coming back for the second run, wonderful piece of fielding.
cut away to the sweeper in the deep on the off side.
played to short fine leg and another tight run.
turned down to fine leg and they are coming back for the second run, good running this time.
comes forward and defends to mid-off.
comes forward and defends with a straight bat to the off side.
good ball and Dowlin is forced to defend.
uses his feet and looks to go big, the spin misses the bat and Dowlin takes it on the pad, an unusual shot at the moment.
turned away to midwicket for a single.
comes forward and defends watchfully to the onside.
moves back and punches it  down the track.
works to midwicket and looks for the single, sent back as the ball goes straight to the fielder.
quicker delivery and straight on the stumps, defended.
turned away through forward of square leg for a single.
driven firmly down the ground to long off for a single.
good ball tossed up bit fuller, almost yorked himself, digs it out to the off side.
worked to midwicket for a single.
moves back and forces it down the ground to long off.
moves forward and works it down the ground to long on.
turns it to the onside.
plays it past the short fine leg and good running, gets the third run.
tossed down the leg side, worked through midwicket for a single.
turns it behind square leg for a single.
plays to short fine leg.
turned away to the deep for a single on the onside.
width outside the off stump and Reifer slices it in the air to backward point, Shakib Al Hasan forward and bit to the right to take a good catch.
comes forward and defends
drives to long-off for a single
on the leg stump. Turned away to deep square leg for a single
comes forward and pushes it to midwicket
on the leg stump.Turned away to deep square leg for a couple
pushes it to long-on for a single
wide down the leg side and Rahim appeals. For what is the question
pushes it to midwicket for a single
comes forward and pushes it to leg side
outside off and arm-ball. Would have been going down leg
comes down the track and looks to loft it away. Bernard is struck on the pads
pushes it to midwicket for a single
on the leg stump. Bernard lofts it away to wide long-on for a boundary
comes forward and defends into the leg side
on the leg stump. Bernard lofts it away to deep square leg for a boundary
pushes to midwicket and runs across for a quick single
comes forward and forces it to midwicket
outside off. Pushes to point for a single
cut to short third man for a single
wide down the leg side. Batsman run across for a single as well
off the top-edge to short fine-leg for a single
pushes it to long-on
driven to sweeper cover for a single
plays with soft hands to cover
driven down the ground to long on for a single.
full toss driven down the ground once again to long on.
moves forward and drives down the ground to long off.
spins way down the leg side.
whacks it past the fielder at midwicket to the deep.
spins down leg, takes the pad this time.
turned to short fine leg.
cuts and misses outside the off stump.
too full for the drive, digs it out and ball goes past the batsman to the keeper who gets rid of the stumps, but the batsman is in.
cut through point, a misfield as the fielder dives over the ball.
plays it behind square leg to pick up a single.
works it once again behind square leg for another single.
driven well this time down the ground to long off, coming back for the second run and Razzak fails to hold onto the ball and missed a good run out chance.
turns it around behind square leg for a single.
full delivery driven down the ground to long on.
moves back and punches to the onside to midwicket.
moves back and defends to the onside.
works it to square leg to pick up a single.
moves forward and drives down the ground to long on.
comes forward and defends down the track.
works it off the front foot behind square leg for a single.
sweeps it down to fine leg for couple of runs and Dowlin gets to his 50 of 88 balls.
works it forward of square leg to pick up a single.
comes forward and defends to the off side.
comes forward and plays square of the wicket on the off side.
mistimes the cut to the off side for a single.
looking for a big shot, could not connect it, mistimes it beside the track on the off side and takes off for a quick single.
again looking for the big shot from outside the off side to the onside, mishits it midwicket outside the inner circle, coming back for the second run.
uses his feet and takes it on the full and drives to deep backward point.
quicker delivery outside the off stump and Bernard leaves his crease and comes down the track and completely misses the ball, Rahim collects the ball and gets rid of the stumps.
moves forward and drives to extra cover.
looking for the big shot on the onside, miscues it behind square leg for a single.
moves forward and drives to the right of mid-on for a single.
down the track and hits it down the ground to long off.
goes all the way for maximum, right in the slot for Lewis, who launches it down the ground and over long on, good strike that.
a leading edge along the track back to the bowler.
played along the ground to extra cover.
reverse sweeps to short third man.
driven off the back foot to the off side.
dropped, driven in the air towards extra cover and Shakib fails to hold onto to a tough chance.
this time he connects well and over long on fence for maximum, good striking by Dowlin.
good shot once again, this time hits it wide of long on for another boundary.
works it past the fielder at short fine leg for couple more runs.
down the wicket and mistimes the cut to cover.
moves back and forces it off the back foot through cover.
good shot from Dowlin, picks his spot nicely and hits it well in the air and to the midwicket fence.
punches off the back foot to the sweeper cover.
forces off the back foot and down the ground to long on for a single.
whacks it from outside the off stump to deep midwicket, comes back for the second run.
mishit down the ground to long on, was looking to go through the off side.
boundaries raining here, swings it forward of square leg and the ball beats the fielder running around.
makes room and hits it well over extra cover, wonderful shot to the fence, this is good stuff from Dowlin.
makes room and cuts hard behind point for a single.
fires it full and down the leg side, signalled a wide.
moves back and drives it down the ground to deep mid-on for a single.
whacks it down the ground to long on.
full on the pads and they scamper through for a leg bye.
slower delivery played down to mid-off for a single.
nudges it to square leg for a single.
low full toss played behind square leg.
looking for the reverse sweep, he does not connect it, off the glove the ball rolls along to the keeper.
full toss and Dowlin hits it well in the gap and to the midwicket fence, the fielder running around cannot stop it.
goes all the way for maximum, another wonderful strike, Lewis swings it high and over the fielder at deep midwicket.
played back to the bowler.
makes room and plays to the sweeper cover.
taps it slowly to the onside and good running, comes back for the second run.
makes room and cuts to point.
looking to force it through the off side, the ball comes slowly off the track and he can only play back to the bowler.
makes room and drives to the sweeper on the off side.
full delivery driven down the ground to long on and Dowlin moves onto 95.
cleans him up, Lewis plays all across the delivery looking to hoick it to the midwicket fence, the slower delivery works for Rasel and the stumps are shattered.
full delivery driven through the off side through cover for a single.
works it through square leg and the ball is just outside the circle, he comes back for the second run, taking on the fielder.
dropped, a difficult return catch to Rasel to his right, Dowlin was looking to work it through midwicket, but played too early.
mishit down the ground to wide long on for couple more.
cuts and gets the edge to the third man fence, bat being thrown left, centre and right, good going this by West Indies.
edges it past the stumps and to the keeper.
swings and misses and Rahim is quickly onto the bowl to prevent any run, well done.
good strike by Sammy, connects it well over the bowler and to the fence.
another full delivery driven down the ground to long off.
pushed straight to the fielder at extra cover.
plays to cover and takes off for a tight single, Dowlin gets his maiden century, well played, raises his bat to the crowd.
too short and too wide, cut away in the air over extra cover for a boundary.
cut away behind point to the deep, comes back for the second run.
short ball pulled away nicely in the gap at midwicket for another boundary, wonderful hitting from Sammy.
yorker delivery squeezed out square of the wicket on the off side.

inn2.comm: starts off with a outswinging yorker and Tamim squeezes it out past backward point
watchfully left alone outside off, good carry to the keeper
digs it in short and Junaid flirts with it outside off lucky not to get an edge
very close to a beamer, but legal enough for the umpire, the batsman pushes it to the off side
too close to cut, he chops it back to the bowler
full outside off and driven firmly to mid-off
Tonge bowls it short and hits the deck hard, he swishes at it and misses
gives him a hint of width outside off and he chops it down to point
raw pace, bounce and he forces the batsman to sway backwards, that travelled quickly
makes the batsman hop at the crease, he improvises by angling it away wide of backward point
back of a length, he hops and carves it to point
pitching outside leg and it comes back in to rap him on the pads as he tries to work it away, stifled appeal but that can't be given
short of a good length just on the off and shooting away. kept low and had the batsman in trouble as he bent low to reach for it, was beaten

banged in short on middle, pulled away in front of square, hesitation as he runs for the second to the non-striker's end but the throw from the deep is wayward and raps Tamim on the helmet, he almost bumps it onto the stumps but is safe
back of a length just outside off, short, waits for it and chops it behind point for a single
banged in short on middle and off, made way and guided it just wide of gully for a single
back of a length, angling across, defended back to the bowler
banged in short just outside off, makes way to upper cut that over the slips but it's a touch too quick and he fails to make contact
a bit of frustration setting in, pitched short just outside off and it swings away, goes for the pull but he doesn't connect
pitched it up on middle and off, driven on the up towards mid-off
short of a good length on middle and leg, doesn't have an idea where to play at, just fends at it and gets a thick inside edge on the leg side for a single
short of a good length just outside off, jabs it between mid-on and midwicket for a single
short and wide, makes room and he slaps it between cover and mid-off for a couple of runs
short of a good length just outside off, punched off the back foot towards cover
almost dragged it on, short of a good length just outside off, tries to push it off the back foot, gets an inside edge just wide of the stumps
pitched up and he takes advantage, overpitched just outside off, driven firmly through the line just wide of mid-off for a pressure-relieving boundary

pulled away, just wide of the outstretched arms of the square-leg fielder, erred in length there, pitched too short and Junaid is onto it quickly, didn't time it all too well but had enough elevation as well as force on it to take it to the ropes
straying on the pads, missed opportunity as he tries to clip that off his pads, is rapped on the pads, should have got another boundary there
a hint of movement into the batsman from a good length outside off, is taken by surprise, fends it away but gets an inside edge into his ribs
short of a length just outside off, dabbed down to third man for a single
hitting across the line, fullish, just outside off, swats it and mistimes it past midwicket for another run
the offcutter, cut away from a good length outside off, reached for it to run it down towards third man, playing away from his body and he missed
pulled away firmly this time but straight to mid-on, not too short but he seems to favour this shot
lands fullish on middle and off, pushed to Dowlin at mid-on who hurls down the stumps at the striker's end, the direct hit is met with huge cheers from this expectant crowd
there is protection in the deep, bowled it short and it's pulled away straight to midwicket, stylishly done but it didn't pace away as he wanted it to
starts off short outside off, its pulled away through the vacant midwicket region for a couple of runs
short of a good length outside off, pushed back to the bowler
slightly short on the off stump, punched from the crease towards deep cover for a single
missed out. short outside off, pulled away straight to square leg, he's not timing it too well is Tamim
mistimes it again, slower one pitched just outside off, drags an attempted heave through square leg and midwicket for a couple
offcutter bowled from outside leg stump, dropped short of point for a single

missed run out, short of a good length on the off, moves back and punches it hard past cover, or so we think as it's not timed well, was struggling to make it to the other end and a direct hit would have had him
slightly short on middle, pushed away off the back foot wide of midwicket for a single
finally manages something, it's full and wide, makes room and slices it away well over point for a boundary
miscues a swing this time, it's pitched up and is there to hit but again he mistimes it wide of mid-on, was uppish and was lucky it was wide of the fielder, Tami's been rusty
full and wide, makes room thinking of going for another forceful stroke but withdraws at the last moment
good length on middle and off, flicked away through to deep square leg for a single
oooh, almost, slower one bowled short outside off, didn't come on, tried to slog it over midwicket but ended up slapping it uppishly but just inches short of mid-on, lucky again
looked ridiculous, short, slower one again, cuts away and beats his attempted heave, almost fell over
short on middle and off, is watchful this time, pushing it off the back foot to mid-off
slower one on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler with a full face, off the middle there
slower one again, this time it's full outside off, eased between point and cover for a single
bad bounce for the fielder at point as the batsman steers it wide of him, they get a single
banged in short on middle, waits for it and ducks in time
fullish on the pads, flicked away uppishly short of deep midwicket for a single
pitched up on middle and leg, flicked away towards deep midwicket, this time all along the ground for a single
it's slowing up this pitch, not coming on, full and wide and he goes hard at it but it ends up rolling down towards point
smashed it hard this time, pitched up and he's on it, drilling it past the bowler wide of mid-on for a boundary, off the middle it came and he'll feel more confident now
loosener and wide down the leg side, lets it go
short on leg stump, tries to crash it through the leg-side field, rapped on the pads and drops into the off side, Tamim calls for a single and is halfway down the pitch but is sent back in time

too well timed for his liking as he finds the fielder in the deep, full on the pads and he flicks it elegantly straight down Kemar Roach's throat at deep midwicket, there was cover there and he knew it and yet attempted a risky shot in that direction, not wise at all, West Indies have struck
full on the off stump, watches it onto his bat and taps it to cover
just wide of the off stump and he held back the length just a touch, defended to cover
angling it in on middle and leg, turned away wide of square leg to get off the mark
fullish on the pads, tries to glance it down fine, is hit on the pads
yorker length just outside off, its full and he fails to get his bat down in time
overpitched and he tries to smack that through the covers but with no footwork, just a swing of the bat and it zips past him
angling it down the pads and a bit of movement takes it further down, fails to get his bat to it as he tries to clip it fine, gets a wide
fails to work this one on the pads away and is struck, calls for a legbye but Ashraful sends him back
picked it up beautifully, pitched up outside off and he presented the full face, chipping it over mid-on for a boundary, sweetly timed
full on the pads and he glances it straight o short fine leg, fell just short of him
wild swing this time, lands on a good length outside off, mistimes, he'll be familiar with that word by now, it to deep midwicket
gives him the charge and tries to clear midwicket but yet again he doesn't connect well, gets an inside edge to short fine leg, scratchy again
slower one down the leg side, beats Tamim's bat as he tries to clip it past short fine and the keeper as it spins away from him as he bends low to pouch that, five runs gifted
slower one on the leg stump, swats it down the ground to long-on for a single
full just outside off, driven straight to cover from the crease
good length outside off, appeared to be bowled at normal pace but it got to the keeper on the second bounce, not good signs
slightly short outside off, slashed away wide of point but a dive keeps them down to a single, dived full length to his left there, saved a couple of runs
length ball on the pads and he clips it away through square leg for a single
full toss on leg stump, driven through wide of long-on for a single
good length on middle and leg, pushed from the crease to mid-on
full on the pads, clipped away off his pads through square leg for a single

superb catch, Ian Bishop can't control himself in the commentary box, perhaps Tamim's best timed shot of the innings, it's full on middle and off, he picks it up beautifully and clips it wide of midwicket but there's Bernard who flings himself to his left to pluck that out of thin air one-handed to end the batsman's nervy stay at the crease
full outside off, almost yorker length, dug out wide of cover
lands on a good length outside off, bunts it through cover and point for a single
angling it in from wide of the crease to midwicket, calls for a single and is sent back, attempt at hurling down the stumps at the striker's end but he makes it back just in time
short of a good length on the off, waits at the crease and dabs it back to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot wide of mid-off for a single
short of a length on leg stump, turns it down towards fine leg for a single
fullish on the off, bumps it to short cover and gets the crowd excited as they think it's a catch, but at 15 overs it's West Indies who have the edge
short on the off, waits for it at the crease and drops it towards cover
slower one bowled short of a length outside off, crashes it through to deep cover for a single
banged in short on middle, a bouncer, goes for the pull but it's too high
slightly short outside off, tapped towards point from the crease
slower one again, offcutter, chopped down to point from the crease
short of a good length on the off, punched uppishly past the bowler towards long-off for a single
nicely played, knew the field, the third man is up and he made room and cut that short one through short third and point for a boundary
the ball's not travelling, pitched up outside off, slower through the air, drilled wide of long-off for a single
angling it full on the pads, turned away towards midwicket, wristily done but he can't get it past him
angling it in towards middle and leg, worked away wide of short fine
short of a length just outside off, guided down to third man for a single
length ball on middle, driven through the line to long-on for a single
pushed into the leg side towards long-on for a single
slightly short on the off, chopped down to point from the crease
short and wide, makes room and cuts it away straight to point
tossed up outside off, reaches forward and defends it watchfully back to the bowler
tossed it up, full outside off, pushed it through cover for a single
on middle an leg, pushed from the crease towards mid-on
short and wide, tries to cut it away through point, doesn't make contact
full outside off, steered it down to third man for a single
banged in short outside leg stump, helps it on its way wide of fine leg for couple of runs
back of a length just outside off, pulled all the way down to deep midwicket for a single
slower offcutter on middle and leg, worked away through square leg for a single
pushed through quick on middle, defended to cover from the crease

poor cricket all round, run out missed, tossed up on middle, mistimes a slog sweep just short of mid-on and Dowlin hurls a throw at the non-striker's end which is ridiculously wayward, Raqibul was miles down the pitch and was a gonner if that had hit
swept down through square leg for a single
short of a length outside off, shot away wide of long-off for a single
tossed up outside off, pushed through to long-off for a single
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and whips it away stylishly through square leg for a single
targeting the blockhole on middle, dug out in time back to the bowler
landed on a good length on middle and leg, pushed through to mid-on from the crease, thinks of a single but it's not available
stump-to-stump, good length just on the off, drops it short of cover and calls for a single again but it's not there
the pressure builds, short and wide, reaches for it and chops it down to point, can't beat the field and it's another dot ball
short of a length outside off, deals with it well this time, cut it away hard wide of point for a well-run couple

Mid-on is up and he goes for it, was tossed up and it landed full on the off stump, tried to slog-sweep it over midwicket but was a slight miscue which landed safe in the direction of long-on, couple more
flighted outside off, makes room and crashes it through cover, it's wide of long-off and he gets two more
flighted on middle and leg, swept down to square leg for a single
trying to get a move-on now, chipped it back over the bowler's head, long-on takes a while to run in and cut it off, two more
drops it short just outside off, spins away and he chops it down towards deep point for  a single
Raqibul likes to sweep and he uses it again, full on middle and leg, plays it down to deep square leg for one more
short of a good length on the off stump, rocks back and defends it solidly back to the bowler
lands on a good length just outside off, turned away through square leg for a single, nicely done
good running, went back and dropped it short of cover, called and the response was spontaneous, what's more, they get overthrows
slower ball bowled fullish on middle and leg, turned away wide of midwicket for a single, gently done
a hint of movement into the batsman, he had opened up but covered it well as it darted back in, bunting it back to the bowler
short of a good length just outside off, moves across to turn it past square leg but was struck high on the pads
just out of reach of the diving point, short outside off, a bit of bounce as he tried to cut that away, got more elevation than he would have wanted and he's lucky that was in the gap
smacked back to the bowler from the crease
quicker through the air, drops it just short of cover and calls for a single but its impossible
short of a length outside off, didn't spin, bunts it off the back foot toward deep cover for a couple more
tossed it up just outside off, a little airy as he crashes that past the bowler towards long-off
tossed up, lands full just outside off, pushed through to the bowler
delicately done, short and wide, waits for it, hangs his bat out at the last moment for a single to third man
short of a length outside off, tries to run it down to third man, chops it down to the keeper
angling it in from outside off, taps it down off the face towards third man and calls for the second but isn't there
kept really low that one and struck him hard on the pads but would have been sliding down, he tried to work it away, gets a leg bye instead
back of a length on the off, gets back and drops it down on the pitch
beaten, pushed through a little quicker this time, full outside off, Raqibul gets close and tries to steer it behind point, doesn't make contact
back of a length outside off, slapped away down to deep cover for a single, Lewis slips in the deep but has his body behind the ball, the slight lapse enables the batsmen to come back for the second
angling it in towards middle and leg, worked away off the pads wide of midwicket for a single
fullish outside leg stump, tries to clip it fine, misses as it brushes the pads on the way to the keeper
angling in towards middle and off, gets forward and pushes it with a straight bat back to the bowler
gone! Slower one bowled on a good length outside off, pushes through the line and does so uppishly, straight to Reifer who bends low to accept a straightforward catch
short of a good length outside off, cut away straight to point from the crease
banged in short on leg stump, helped on its way to fine leg for a single
landed on a good length on middle and leg, pushed towards mid-on from the crease

missed run-out, zipped through really quickly, came back in from outside off, dabbed just wide of the keeper and he rushes through for a single, though he was gone if Thomas' attempt at a direct hit at the non-striker's end had been successful
short of a length outside off, guided down to third man for a single
is nicely into the pull, rolls his wrists over it beautifully, just erred in length and he got into a good position to play it wide of deep square leg for a couple
short of a length outside off, slapped, swatted the ball like a fly down to long-off for a single
length ball outside off, swipes it away through square leg for a single
landed on a good length outside off, chopped down to point
good length on middle, worked in front of square for a single
full on the off, leant into the drive towards long-off for a single
a boundary at last, short and wide, in the zone for the batsman who makes room and beats point with a fierce cut through to the boundary
on middle and off, uses his wrists well to turn it towards square leg for a single
four more, angling it on the pads, full down the leg side and Ashraful has no trouble dispatching it to the fine-leg boundary
short and wide, reaches for a cut, its too wide and he makes contact
full toss on middle, worked away to deep square leg for a single

beamer, slipped out, called a no-ball and Roach has quickly apologized, will get a warning nevertheless, another extra run, the keeper fumbled and they get another one, Sammy ducks as well, at square leg, even he felt he was in the firing zone
short of a length, and wide, slashed down to third man for a single, Shakib's positive as ever
Ashraful's looked good, waited for it, it was a touch wide and he guided it calmly down to third man for a single
short of a length outside off, bunts it off the back foot down to deep cover for one more, rotating the strike well
down the leg side again but the umpire doesn't call it a wide, brushed the pads on the way to the keeper apparently
tossed it up outside off, swiped it cross batted down to deep midwicket for a couple
the googly, spun away and Shakib checked his shot there, jabbed it towards deep midwicket for a single

Big one! Gets to his half-century in style, tossed up outside off, lands full, makes room and clears long-off after hitting it inside out, not by much though, just about but he gets to his second consecutive fifty
fullish just outside off, made room and sliced it over point for a single

four more, tossed up outside off and Shakib is a powerful slog-sweeper, just manages to clear midwicket to strike it to the ropes, the pressure has come off slightly and Lewis has conceded 14 off the over
short of a length from wide of the crease, dabbed it down at the last moment for a single to third man, has used that shot frequently, and well
fullish outside off, came front and across and tried to slog it past the bowler but didn't connect well at all

it pays off this time, he's hurled it on a length again, it's wide and he has a free swing of the arms, crashing it through midwicket for a boundary, in attacking mode is the Bangladesh captain and he's done superbly
targeting the blockhole on the off, digs it out in the direction of long-off for a single
short of a length just outside off, moves away and cuts it past point for a single
fullish on middle and off, presents the full face of the bat as he drives it down the ground to long-off for a single
shortish outside off, pats it wide of midwicket into the outfield for a single
short of a length just outside off, chopped down to point from the crease
flighted just outside leg stump, turns in to strike him high on the pads as he tries to turn it away
short outside off, punches it towards deep cover for a single
he googly, Shakib misses it as he expects it to turn in and go for a sweep square
quicker and flat just outside off, comes down the pitch and pushes it past the bowler towards long-off for a single
just short of a good length on middle, pushed down towards long-on for a single
slightly short outside off, waited for it and opened the face to guide it down to third man, the partnership is now worth 51
full toss on the pads, you don't bowl those with the fine-leg up, clipped away wide of deep square leg for a single
four runs gifted, was too early into the shot as he tried to cut the slower one, he missed and so did the keeper Thomas who failed to get his body behind the ball
back of a length just outside off, slapped down the ground to long-off
short and wide and that run down to third man again, nicely done, keeps the strike
short and wide, cut away down to third man from the crease, single taken
slightly short on the off, moves across and pushes it through midwicket, there's a big gap there and he has enough time to come back for the second
short on the off, moves across and slaps it back to the bowler
short of a good length on leg stump, pushed away off the back foot towards midwicket for a single
lands on a good length on leg stump, worked away behind square for a single, or so it seemed, it clipped the pads
full outside leg stump, turned away hard off the back foot but straight to deep square leg for a single
the googly, short and wide, reaches for it to play the cut but makes no contact
another one, short and wide, tries to cut it hard behind point but the away spin takes it further from him
turned back in sharply, waited for it, and chopped it just at the last moment behind point for a single
on middle and leg, turned it away just wide of Miller at short fine, calls for a single and receives a quick response, the fielder, though, fumbles it
flighted just outside off, pushed it back towards the bowler
gets forward and cracks it wide of the bowler towards mid-off for a quick single
on middle and leg, whipped away off the pads towards deep midwicket for a single
good length from wide of the crease angling it into the off stump, defended rock solid back to the bowler
aggression, short and wide, moved away and slashed it away towards third man who's been pushed back now for the right hander
the offcutter pitched up outside off, driven through the line off the middle of the bat down to long-off for a single
coming in just a hint, got to the pitch and nudged it behind point for a single
banged in short on leg stump, comes forward and jabs it down to long-on for a single to keep the strike, this will do for the visitors
short on the off stump, doesn't spin much, makes room and thrashes that to deep point

big wicket! Ashraful has thrown it away. Tossed it up outside off and he chips it straight down long-off's throat, Dale Richards takes it comfortably and West Indies have fought back, loose shot and he pays the price, could that be turning point?
pushed through quick outside off, goes for the cut but makes no contact
pitched it up outside off, tries to drive through straight but it's the googly and it takes the thick outside edge to roll down behind point for a single
flighted outside off, waited for it, dabs it towards point, calls for a single but it's not there

almost lobbed it back, tossed it up and he got to the pitch to turn it past the bowler with a closed face but it almost caught the leading edge and fell short, just short, of Lewis. Ends a successful over.
full on middle, drilled it down the ground past the bowler wide of long-off for a couple, accurate throw in the end but Mushfiqur was quick
short of a good length outside off, dropped it short of extra cover and rushed through for a single
fullish outside off, steered it down to third man for a single
full on middle, driven back forcefully but straight to the bowler
pitched up but a little wide this time, played it through the line towards long-off for a single
overpitched and driven into the ground straight to extra cover, the crowd thinks he's gone
flighted it outside off, drew him out of the crease, crashed down the ground towards long-off for a single
went for the sweep but ti was much shorter than he would have wanted, struck the top of the arm and fell just wide of the diving keeper
leading edge, he's living dangerously, spun away sharply as he played at it across the line, got the leading edge right between cover and point
the googly, he spotted it, waiting for it to turn away and pushed him past extra cover for a single
tossed it up outside off, guided straight to point, the nerves are back
length ball on the off, stands tall and drives it hard down the ground to long-off, gets his team to 200
dropped his wrists at the right time to run it down to third man for a single, Shakib thought of a second but it simply wasn't there
hitting a good length and its straight, just punches it back to the bowler, dot ball
fullish outside off, thumps it down the ground to long-off for a single
fullish outside off, drops it short of cover and scampers down the pitch for a quick single
another quick run, driven just wide of extra cover who's at the edge of the circle and they just about have enough time to complete the single

chaos, utter chaos! Tossed it up just outside off, came down the track and tried to clear long-off, miscued it completely and landed bang in between Sammy running back from extra cover and Bernard running in from long-off, they collide and are both down, Shakib gets to his fifty as they run three, and they haven't got up yet
waited for it to turn from middle towards off and pushed it short of midwicket for a single
down the leg side this time, pitched outside leg and turned down further, called a wide
slightly short on leg stump, jabbed wide of short fine for a quick single
turned away from a good length outside off, came forward, outside the line and padded it away
short and wide, cracked down towards deep cover for a single
fullish outside off, pushed it through the line towards long-off for a single
starts with a wide, too wide, Shakib promptly lets it go and wins a run
fullish on middle and leg, turned away through square leg for a single and the fielder in the deep fumbles, though they looked good to come back for the second anyway
bowled on a length outside off, driven through the line to long-off for a single
short of a good length on middle, turned away to deep square leg for a single
full toss, a low one on leg stump, driven to Sammy at midwicket who backs out of the throw as his hamstring stings him again
slightly short outside off, nudged it behind point for an easy single, much better from Mushfiqur after that nervy start
full outside off, doesn't get hold of an attempted swing through midwicket, calls for a single but the bowler recovers well to prevent it
four, sensed a chance with a ball that was pitched up outside off, moved away and swung it over midwicket for a boundary
four more, they are getting closer, full toss outside off, slashes hard, gets a thick edge well wide of the keeper to the third-man boundary
fullish outside off, goes at it hard, square-drives it to point and Sammy fumbles to allow them a quick single, returns a wayward throw as well but no more damage done

Shakib swings hard this time, full on the pads, clipped over square leg, Reifer gives chase and drags it just back in, throws a wide return to Roach and Shakib is way down the pitch calling for the third, by the time hurls it back to the keeper the Bangladesh captain has made it in time
full on middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler

Six, and he's off the attack for that was above waist height! Slipped out of his fingers, chest high full toss outside leg stump and Shakib dismisses it, moving across, to the fine-leg boundary, seven runs in all given that was a no-ball, what a costly over. He's off the attack because he's bowled two full tosses above waist height, you are only allowed one slip up.
round the wicket and bowls it on a length just on middle and off, pushed down wide of mid-on for a single to keep the strike

he's struck! Is there another twist to this tale? Full and wide, swings hard across the line, gets a thick edge and Dale Richards at short third man takes a good low catch just inches off the ground, big wicket!
angling it in on the pads, tries to turn it pan, clipped his pads on the way just wide of short fine, they take a quick single
wide, though it came back in, but too lat, it had passed the batsman
short on middle and leg, hit high on the pads and he tries to scramble down thepitch but the bowler recovers well to keep him put
full outside off, swung away over square leg for a couple of runs
in the blockhole outside off, dug out back to the bowler
length ball well wide of off, Mushfiqur drags it down to long-on for a single, we are set for a tight finish now with Shakib gone, what a crucial blow
down the leg side, hurled short, a wide at a crucial time, a run gifted, you cannot afford to do that at this stage of the innings
short outside off, pulled just wide of midwicket for a quick single, dives full length to make it back
angling it on the pads, flicked away just wide of square leg for a single
swung across the line and some good fielding from Kieran Powell, the substitute fielder at square leg, saves a few runs, keeps them down to a single as he dives full length to his right
poor bowling, down the leg side, another wide, which side is choking here? Bangladesh are slowing down, but West Indies are gifting them with runs off extras
yorker length on leg stump, dug out in front of midwicket for another quick single, they haven't scored too many direct hits have West Indies
full on the pads, flicked away stylishly but Devon Smith fields well stretching to his left at short fine leg to keep them down to a single
on target, finally, bowled on a good length on middle, pushed past the bowler for a single in the direction of long-on

he's struck off his second ball in ODIs! Bowled full on middle and off, tried to shuffle across and glance it fine, it caught the top edge and Nikita Miller took a well-judged catch running to his left
low full toss outside off, stroked straight to cover
strays on his pads and he takes advantage, flicking it away behind square to beat fine leg to the boundary, that should ease the nerves a little, a gift ball but you've got to dismiss them

Four more! Wide of the crease and angling it straight into his pads, Mushfiqur repeats the shot with a bit more elevation this time to beat deep square leg to the ropes, you can't stick to that line with the fine leg brought up
follows that up with a wide, too wide and another run gifted, undermining that wicket off the first ball of the over
another one, Mushfiqur shoulders arms and the umpire stretches his, way wide of the off stump, this is poor stuff
forces it quick, draws him into the drive and he is beaten

Another twist! Poor cricket all around, except the catch, juicy full toss outside off and Mushfiqur plays a powerful drive but fails to keep it down, smashing it straight to Sammy who takes it over his head, timing his jump perfectly, to make things even more interesting
landing on a good length on leg stump, pushed off the back foot behind square for a single, was actually struck on his thighs as he shuffled across
fullish on middle and off, pushed wide of midwicket for a single and he hurls an overthrow to give them one more, not the best cricket this
short of a good length outside off, turned his bat to guide that down to third man for a single
fullish on the off stump, got across and played with the bat really close to the pads, defending it on the leg side
pushed into the off side towards point and they make it through for for a quick single
overpitched outside off, driven towards mid-off for a single to keep the strike
dropped, short outside off, slapped hard just wide of Sammy who stretches well to his left but fails to latch on, tough chance on the follow through
yorker length just outside off, dug out  back to the bowler
landed on a good length outside off, flirting with the ball there and he misses
three crucial runs, releases the pressure, length ball outside off, goes at it hard, manages to clear the in-field over extra cover and mid-off, they inch closer to the target
good length on middle and off, pushed wide of the bowler from the crease, decide against the single
Pushed away into the off side wide of cover for a single, waited for it and just nudged it past the fielder to keep the strike
angling it in towards middle and off, defended towards cover
fullish on middle and leg, defends it with a straight bat back to the bowler
pitched up on the pads, he prefers to finish this in singles, pushed gently just wide of midwicket for a run, three more for a win now
full and wide, smashed it into the ground towards mid-off, struck firmly but found the fielder
the nerves build as he tries to slap that over the bowler's head, short outside off and he makes no contact
the freakish end to the game typifies the innings, short and wide, swings across the line, gets a thick edge over short third man for a boundary, Bangladesh win the series
